headline: APH Q1 Earnings Call: IT Datacom Drives Revenue Upside While Guidance Lags Expectations
summary: Electrical connector manufacturer Amphenol (NYSE:APH) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 47.7% year on year to $4.81 billion. On the other hand, next quarter’s revenue guidance of $4.95 billion was less impressive, coming in 1.3% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.63 per share was 21.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
